{
  "stem": "15768.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And although it was a very frightening experience, it came to a, and OK ending.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then shortly thereafter, the word went forth that anybody was not a French citizen had to return to their place of origin.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And these were signs on trees and poles or whatever there might have been.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was no escaping this edict.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And my father again pondered and pondered and decided there was no way that he was going to go back anywhere-- not Brussels or anywhere else-- and decided again if there was any way-- of course, France had capitulated at that point.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It is now the end of July, 1940.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] my father still felt, even though probably the relatives would have been gone from Paris, that he was going to try for Paris once more and to pick up some sort of a connection.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And so first, he went out and we sampled bicycles for two for my father and my mother.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Because my mother couldn't ride a bicycle.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "But then it was really so difficult and my brother couldn't master a bicycle.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So we aborted that scheme.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And it was a short train ride from Boulogne-sur-Mer to Lille, which was the nearest big city.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And with trepidations, we boarded the train.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we went to Lille.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "In Lille, again, it was not a quiet town.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "We-- we stayed in a chintzy hotel.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And during the night, there was a gunshot through the window-- not directed at us, I'm sure, but just some scuffle that was going on in town.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And then after a day in Lille, my father said he was going somewhere to meet someone.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And he would be back.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
